<p>So, what formula is there for this shape?</p>
<pre>I used calculus, though it probably wasn't entirely necessary, to find=
 a formula for this sort of shape where two rectangles are joined by straig=
ht edges, without having to be a frustum, and I got this:

                  a2
              +-------+
           b2/       / \---------
            +-------+   \      |
           /        |    \     |
          /.........|.... +    | h
         /          |    /     |
        /           |   /      |
       /            |  /b1 ------
      /             | /
     /              |/
    +---------------+
           a1

     V =3D [a1*b1 + a2*b2 + (a1*b2 + a2*b1)/2] * h/3

Here the bottom is a1 x b1, and the top is a2 x b2, with the a's parallel a=
nd the b's parallel. Notice that a1*b1 =3D B1 and a2*b2 =3D B2 in the frust=
um formula; but the third term "averages" the two in a different way, which=
 works out to be the same if a1/b1 =3D a2/b2. Try both formulas for your sh=
ape, and you'll find they give different results.</pre>
